    <item>
      <title></title>
      <link>https://people.csail.mit.edu/weifang/authors/admin/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 01 Sep 2021 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://people.csail.mit.edu/weifang/authors/admin/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;I&amp;rsquo;m a 5th year PhD student in the Spoken Language Systems Group at MIT CSAIL, working with &lt;a href=&#34;http://people.csail.mit.edu/jrg/&#34;&gt;Dr. James Glass&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I am currently working on conversational AI, including but not limited to
language understanding, question answering, information retrieval and extraction.
I&amp;rsquo;m generally interested in machine learning for NLP and improving NLP agents&#39;
reasoning and logical capabilities.
Previously I have worked on various projects on language and speech,
including temporal relation extraction, automatic fact-checking, and end-to-end speech synthesis.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;During my undergrad studies at National Taiwan University (NTU), I researched on speech and language understanding under &lt;a href=&#34;http://speech.ee.ntu.edu.tw/~tlkagk/&#34;&gt;Prof. Hung-Yi Lee&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&#34;http://speech.ee.ntu.edu.tw/previous_version/lslNew.htm&#34;&gt;Prof. Lin-Shan Lee&lt;/a&gt;, and worked on machine learning problems for computer vision under &lt;a href=&#34;http://vllab.ee.ntu.edu.tw/members.html&#34;&gt;Prof. Yu-Chiang Frank Wang&lt;/a&gt; at Academia Sinica/NTU. I also interned twice with the NLP team at Apple in California.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Here is my &lt;a href=&#34;files/resume.pdf&#34;&gt;Curriculum Vitae (updated Nov 2022)&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
